TI  - Preparation and characterization of La/g-C3N4/TiO2 quantum dots and their detection of FLE-Induced degradation: A bifunctional study and its correlation with traditional Chinese medicine antitumor therapy applications
PY  - 2026
T2  - Journal of the Indian Chemical Society
VL  - 103
IS  - 4
C7  - 102510
DO  - 10.1016/j.jics.2026.102510
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-105030980173&doi=10.1016%2Fj.jics.2026.102510&partnerID=40&md5=cb66090ff7606c464c1f85823edbc775
AB  - Fleroxacin (FLE), a third-generation fluoroquinolone, is widely used in infection prevention for intestinal tumor patients but its residues in the intestinal microenvironment disrupt the efficacy of the classic traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) regimen—Jiawei Huaihua Powder (JHP) combined with Purgation Method (PM)—by disturbing gut microbiota and interacting with JHP active components. To address this bottleneck for the mechanism study of JHP-PM in intestinal tumor treatment, we prepared La/g-C3N4 co-doped TiO2 (GLT) quantum dots via a two-step sol-gel method using tetrabutyl titanate as precursor and melamine as C/N source. For detection, FLE quenched GLT's phosphorescence, enabling a rapid FLE determination method. Under optimal conditions, the phosphorescent quenching signal (P0/P) showed a good linear relationship with FLE concentration in the range of 0.5–50 μg/mL (correlation coefficient r = 0.997), with a relative standard deviation (RSD) of 3.8% and a detection limit of 0.11 μg/mL. Selectivity tests with JHP active components (rutin, quercetin, baicalin) confirmed GLT's reliability in JHP-PM-related scenarios. For photocatalysis, 20 mg/L FLE aqueous solution was used as the target pollutant. GLT-mediated FLE degradation followed the pseudo-first-order kinetic model (rate constant k = 0.00439 min−1, R2 = 0.9907), with activity significantly higher than that of pure TiO2 and La/TiO2. This enhancement was attributed to La-induced TiO2 grain refinement (verified by XRD) and g–C3N4–facilitated photogenerated charge separation (confirmed by XPS and fluorescence lifetime analysis). GLT was stable under simulated intestinal pH (6.0–7.5), retaining 90% of its phosphorescent and photocatalytic activity. In summary, this dual-functional GLT system not only provides a novel approach for FLE pollution control but also offers technical support for the in-depth mechanism study of JHP-PM in intestinal tumor treatment, bridging nanomaterial research and TCM-based cancer therapy. © 2026 Indian Chemical Society.
